A Warrant Officer Bhekisigcino Khwela (54) was shot
dead and his son wounded outside his house in KwaNdengezi. Two gunmen, who were on foot reportedly fired several shots
at them the Mariannhill detective was killed instantly. The son was wounded and the friend escaped unscathed. In a separate incident, another policeman, Captain Lumkile
Wiseman Tyibilika was killed in the early hours in New Brighton in the Eastern
Cape. “The motives for both incidents are not conclusive at this
stage but form part of investigations. In both incidents the 72 hour Activation
Plan is being implemented,” Police spokesperson Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo said. "The killing of our two colleagues yesterday is a
reflection of what police must endure on a daily basis", said General
Sitole. "I have instructed the Provincial Commissioners of both
the Eastern Cape and KwaZulu-Natal to mobilise maximum resources to track down
those responsible and bring them to book", added General Sitole. He urged anyone with information on these murders to contact
Crime Stop on 086 00 10111.  